.SH SHMultiTaperMaskSE
Perform a localized multitaper spectral analysis using arbitrary windows
derived from a mask.
.SH Usage
call SHMultiTaperMaskSE (\f[CR]mtse\f[R], \f[CR]sd\f[R],
\f[CR]cilm\f[R], \f[CR]lmax\f[R], \f[CR]tapers\f[R], \f[CR]lmaxt\f[R],
\f[CR]k\f[R], \f[CR]taper_wt\f[R], \f[CR]norm\f[R], \f[CR]csphase\f[R],
\f[CR]exitstatus\f[R])
.SH Parameters
.TP
\f[CR]mtse\f[R] : output, real(dp), dimension (\f[CR]lmax\f[R]\-\f[CR]lmaxt\f[R]+1)
The localized multitaper power spectrum estimate.
.TP
\f[CR]sd\f[R] : output, real(dp), dimension (\f[CR]lmax\f[R]\-\f[CR]lmaxt\f[R]+1)
The standard error of the localized multitaper power spectral estimates.
.TP
\f[CR]cilm\f[R] : input, real(dp), dimension (2, \f[CR]lmax\f[R]+1, \f[CR]lmax\f[R]+1)
The spherical harmonic coefficients of the function to be localized.
.TP
\f[CR]lmax\f[R] : input, integer(int32)
The spherical harmonic bandwidth of \f[CR]cilm\f[R].
.TP
\f[CR]tapers\f[R] : input, real(dp), dimension ((\f[CR]lmaxt\f[R]+1)**2, \f[CR]k\f[R])
An array of the \f[CR]k\f[R] windowing functions, arranged in columns,
obtained from a call to \f[CR]SHReturnTapersMap\f[R].
The spherical harmonic coefficients are packed according to the
conventions in \f[CR]SHCilmToVector\f[R].
.TP
\f[CR]lmaxt\f[R] : input, integer(int32)
The spherical harmonic bandwidth of the windowing functions in the array
\f[CR]tapers\f[R].
.TP
\f[CR]k\f[R] : input, integer(int32)
The number of tapers to be utilized in performing the multitaper
spectral analysis.
.TP
\f[CR]taper_wt\f[R] : input, optional, real(dp), dimension (\f[CR]k\f[R])
The weights used in calculating the multitaper spectral estimates and
